      "writtenOn": "2026-04-02T13:11:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "More info: The core issue is that `internal/diff` operates on two evaluated CUE values. What then happens is that it would basically compare against two evaluated values, possibly papering over bugs. For instance if I compare `*1 | int` against `*1 | 1 | int` to see if the second normalized to the first, I would end up checking `1` against `1`.",
